Q1. What packet does a server normally send in rsponse to a syn?
Ans- It send SYN_ACK packets in return

Q2. Explain why a SYN Flood crashes a server (mention "HAlf_Open Connections").
Ans- In SYN flood the attacker sends a large number of SYN packets but when server sends back SYN_ACK packets then attacker don't sends ACK packets and beacuse of it server's resources gets full and now server cant accepts new request and hence server freezes

Q3. Name one defense technique againts SYN Floods (e.d.,SYN Cookies).
Ans- Reduced SYN-RECIEVED Timer- Decreasing the time the server waits for the final attack from the client frees up resources more quickly from half-open connections
